  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study evaluates the efficiency and the cost of three medical devices and the abstention
      of the use of specific product for the post-operative haemostasis in endonasal surgery .
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Surgiflo® is a matrix of haemostatic frost of porcine protein origin is the coverage of the
      post-operative bleeding of which one of the indications is in endonasal surgery.

      Floseal® is a haemostatic frost(gel) containing of the thrombin.

      Algosteril® is a lint tent of arginate of calcium.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
